        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 6:45AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 645 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
northeast of Cass, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Dutton...                         Cass...
Red Star...                       Pettigrew...
St. Paul...                       Redding...
Weathers...                       Kingston...
Witter...                         Brashears...
Combs...                          Turners Bend...
Taft...                           Boston...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
